# Primitives Only

No imported meshes, no external 3D model files, no texture atlases for in-world objects.

Every ship, dock, building, crate, terrain piece, and prop is constructed in GDScript from Godot primitive meshes with `StandardMaterial3D`.

## The Pattern

```gdscript
var mi := MeshInstance3D.new()
var mesh := BoxMesh.new()
mesh.size = Vector3(2.0, 0.5, 4.0)
mi.mesh = mesh

var mat := StandardMaterial3D.new()
mat.albedo_color = Color(0.35, 0.28, 0.22)
mat.roughness = 0.85
mat.metallic = 0.05
mi.material_override = mat
add_child(mi)
```

## Allowed Primitives

`BoxMesh`, `CylinderMesh`, `SphereMesh`, `CapsuleMesh`, `PlaneMesh`, `PrismMesh`, `TorusMesh`

Use `MeshBuilder` in `scripts/world/mesh_builder.gd` for common compound shapes.

## What Goes in resources/shaders/

Custom `.gdshader` files for water, fog, outlines, etc. Applied to materials at runtime — never imported as textures.

## UI Is Exempt

2D UI (Control nodes, themes, icons) may use imported assets. This rule applies to the 3D world only.
